<keyLead box="[151,1436,940,962]" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">1 Integument without muscle attachment sclerites............................................................. 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,940,1284]" box="[151,1436,969,991]" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,969,991]" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">- Integument with muscle attachment sclerites............................................................... 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="7" pageNumber="150">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,940,1284]" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">
<keyLead pageId="7" pageNumber="150">
2 P-4 shorter than P-3, P-2 distoventral projection bearing three fine setae, P-3 ventral margin straight (
<figureCitation box="[1181,1252,998,1020]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[227,1364,196,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[206,1381,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Sperchon, adults: S. tridentatus: 22, pedipalp; 23, leg claw (after Sokolow 1940); S. minor: 24, idiosoma, dorsal view; 25, idiosoma, ventral view; 26, pedipalp (after Tuzovsky 2003)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756118" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756118/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
), claw lamella with straight ventral margin (
<figureCitation box="[457,528,1028,1050]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[227,1364,196,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[206,1381,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Sperchon, adults: S. tridentatus: 22, pedipalp; 23, leg claw (after Sokolow 1940); S. minor: 24, idiosoma, dorsal view; 25, idiosoma, ventral view; 26, pedipalp (after Tuzovsky 2003)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756118" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756118/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
), excretory pore unsclerotized (
<bibRefCitation author="Sokolow, I. I." box="[832,974,1028,1050]" pageId="7" pageNumber="150" pagination="1 - 511" refId="ref3946" refString="Sokolow, I. I. (1940) [Hydracarina. Part I: Hydrachnellae. In: Fauna of the USSR. Paukoobraznye 5 (2). Nauka, Moscow-Leningrad, pp. 1 - 511. [in Russian]" type="book chapter" year="1940">Sokolow 1940</bibRefCitation>
).......................... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sokolow" authorityYear="1940" box="[1308,1436,1028,1049]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tridentatus">
<emphasis box="[1308,1320,1028,1049]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1332,1436,1028,1049]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">tridentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,940,1284]" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">
<keyLead pageId="7" pageNumber="150">
- P-4 longer than P-3, P-2 with thick seta near base of distoventral projection which bearing two fine setae (
<figureCitation box="[1242,1312,1057,1079]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–21" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1960,1984]" captionTargetBox="[174,1417,1000,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-345@5.[161,1427,992,1937]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 19–21. Sperchon (Sperchon) smiti sp. n., male: 19, pedipalp; 20, IV-Leg-3–6; 21, leg claw. Scale bar: 1, 2, 3–5, 6 = 50 μm, 7, 8 = 20 μm" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756116" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756116/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
), P-3 ventral margin convex, claw lamella with concave ventral margin (
<figureCitation box="[795,866,1086,1108]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–21" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1960,1984]" captionTargetBox="[174,1417,1000,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-345@5.[161,1427,992,1937]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 19–21. Sperchon (Sperchon) smiti sp. n., male: 19, pedipalp; 20, IV-Leg-3–6; 21, leg claw. Scale bar: 1, 2, 3–5, 6 = 50 μm, 7, 8 = 20 μm" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756116" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756116/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
), excretory pore sclerotized (
<figureCitation box="[1146,1216,1086,1108]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[192,1388,391,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-62@4.[182,1406,381,1897]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Sperchon (Sperchon) smiti sp. n., male: 10, fragment of integument; 11, seta Fch; 12, idiocomal seta associated with glandularia; 13, trichobothria Oi; 14, coxal plates, left side; 15, genital field; 16, excretory pore; 17, capitulum, lateral view; 18, chelicera. Scale bars: 10–13, 16 = 50 μm, 14–15, 17–18 = 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756114" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756114/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
)...... 
<taxonomicName authority="Tuzovskij, 2021" authorityName="Tuzovskij" authorityYear="2021" box="[1312,1383,1087,1108]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smiti" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis box="[1312,1383,1087,1108]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">S. smiti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1388,1437,1086,1107]" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1388,1437,1086,1107]" pageId="7" pageNumber="150" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="7" pageNumber="150">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,940,1284]" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">
<keyLead pageId="7" pageNumber="150">
3 All dorsocentral sclerites free and sclerotized (
<figureCitation box="[676,732,1116,1138]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1912,1936]" captionTargetBox="[162,1431,926,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-297@2.[151,1436,921,1889]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Sperchon (Sperchon) pesici sp. n., male: 1, idiosoma dorsal view; 2, idiosoma ventral view. Scale bar: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756110" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756110/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), P-2 with rather long ventrodistal projection bearing two fine setae (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 3–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[166,1426,193,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-15@3.[151,1436,181,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–9. Sperchon (Sperchon) pesici sp. n., male: 3, genital plate; 4, ejaculatory complex; 5, capitulum, lateral view; 6, chelicera, lateral view; 7, pedipalp; 8, IV-Leg-3–6; 9, leg claw. Scale bars: 3, 5–7 = 100 μm, 4 = 200 μm, 9 =50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756112/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
), all genital acetabula subequal in size and distinctly separated (
<figureCitation box="[855,913,1145,1167]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[166,1426,193,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-15@3.[151,1436,181,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–9. Sperchon (Sperchon) pesici sp. n., male: 3, genital plate; 4, ejaculatory complex; 5, capitulum, lateral view; 6, chelicera, lateral view; 7, pedipalp; 8, IV-Leg-3–6; 9, leg claw. Scale bars: 3, 5–7 = 100 μm, 4 = 200 μm, 9 =50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756112/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
), excretory pore (
<figureCitation box="[1084,1142,1145,1167]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1912,1936]" captionTargetBox="[162,1431,926,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-297@2.[151,1436,921,1889]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Sperchon (Sperchon) pesici sp. n., male: 1, idiosoma dorsal view; 2, idiosoma ventral view. Scale bar: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756110" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756110/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) unsclerotized.................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Tuzovskij, 2021" authorityName="Tuzovskij" authorityYear="2021" box="[1296,1376,1175,1196]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pesici" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1296,1308,1175,1196]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1320,1376,1175,1196]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">pesici</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1382,1436,1174,1195]" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1382,1436,1174,1195]" pageId="7" pageNumber="150" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,940,1284]" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">
<keyLead pageId="7" pageNumber="150">
- Dorsocentral sclerites dc.1 and dc.2 unsclerotized, dc.3 fused with glandulartia 
<emphasis box="[995,1024,1204,1225]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">Sci</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1037,1109,1204,1226]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[227,1364,196,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[206,1381,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Sperchon, adults: S. tridentatus: 22, pedipalp; 23, leg claw (after Sokolow 1940); S. minor: 24, idiosoma, dorsal view; 25, idiosoma, ventral view; 26, pedipalp (after Tuzovsky 2003)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756118" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756118/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
), P-2 distoventral projecting short and without fine setae, with single thick seta near base of projection (
<figureCitation box="[916,990,1233,1255]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[227,1364,196,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[206,1381,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Sperchon, adults: S. tridentatus: 22, pedipalp; 23, leg claw (after Sokolow 1940); S. minor: 24, idiosoma, dorsal view; 25, idiosoma, ventral view; 26, pedipalp (after Tuzovsky 2003)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756118" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756118/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
), ac.2 larger than ac.1 and ac.3, all acetabula slightly separated, excretory pore (
<figureCitation box="[559,629,1262,1284]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[227,1364,196,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[206,1381,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Sperchon, adults: S. tridentatus: 22, pedipalp; 23, leg claw (after Sokolow 1940); S. minor: 24, idiosoma, dorsal view; 25, idiosoma, ventral view; 26, pedipalp (after Tuzovsky 2003)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756118" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756118/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
) sclerotized (
<bibRefCitation author="Tuzovskij, P. V." box="[758,910,1262,1284]" pageId="7" pageNumber="150" pagination="215 - 219" refId="ref4060" refString="Tuzovskij, P. V. (2003) Two new species of water mites of the genus Sperchon Kramer (Acariformes, Sperchontidae) from Central Asia. Acarina, 11 (2), 215 - 219." type="journal article" year="2003">Tuzovskij 2003</bibRefCitation>
)................................... 
